      "type": "answer",
      "text": "The Frappe Framework bench is a **complete web application platform** that works like this:\n\n## Architecture Flow:\n\n**1. Frontend (Community Launchpad Prototype):**\n- Vue 3 + TypeScript app running in browser\n- Routes: `/`, `/spaces/:spaceId`, `/events`, `/mentors`, `/messages`, etc.\n- Uses **in-memory mock store** (`src/mock-data/store.ts`)\n- Interacts with Frappe via HTTP API calls\n\n**2. Frappe HTTP API Layer:**\n- `/api/resource/<DocType>` - CRUD operations\n- `/api/method/frappe.client.insert` - Custom whitelists\n- `/api/method/fg_companion.api.<function>` - Custom app endpoints\n\n**3. Frappe Bench (Production Backend):**\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│           Browser (Vue 3 + Vue Router 4)           │\n│                                                     │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n│  │  AppLayout   │  │   Pages /   │  │  Components  │ │\n│  │ (nav, side-  │  │   Routes    │  │ PostCard,    │ │\n│  │  bar, shell) │  │ (16 files)  │  │ SentimentBdg │ │\n│  └──────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────┘ │\n│                     │                               │\n│    ┌───────────────▼────────────────┐               │\n│    │     src/mock-data/store.ts      │  ← Vuex store  │\n│    │  (in-memory reactive store)     │               │\n│    │  seed.ts → typed arrays         │               │\n│    │  types.ts → DocType mirror      │               │\n│    └───────────────────────────────  │               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**4. Frappe Framework Apps:**\n\n**Platform Core (frappe/frappe):**\n- `User` table → Authentication & authorization\n- `Role` table → Permission management\n- `Notification Log` → Push notifications\n- `Email Queue` → Email delivery (digests, events)\n- Background jobs → Scheduled tasks\n\n**Community (frappe/gameplan):**\n- `GP Team` → Space groups\n- `GP Project` → Individual Spaces\n- `GP Discussion` → Posts\n- `GP Comment` → Comments\n- `GP Reaction` → Emoji reactions\n- `GP User Profile` → Member profiles\n\n**Learning (frappe/lms):**\n- `LMS Course` → Course catalog\n- `LMS Chapter` → Course chapters\n- `LMS Lesson` → Course lessons\n- `LMS Enrollment` → Course enrollment\n- `LMS Course Progress` → Progress tracking\n- `LMS Certificate` → Course completion certificates\n\n**Messaging (frappe/raven):**\n- `Raven Channel` → DM channels\n- `Raven Message` → Direct messages\n- Real-time WebSocket updates\n\n**Support (frappe/helpdesk):**\n- `Helpdesk` → Support tickets\n- `Helpdesk Member` → Member support\n- `Safeguarding` → Abuse reporting\n\n**Content (frappe/wiki):**\n- `Wiki Page` → Community handbook\n- Documentation & code of conduct\n\n**Analytics (frappe/insights):**\n- Dashboards → Usage analytics\n- Reports → Member metrics\n\n**Gamification (frappe/eps):**\n- `Energy Point` → Points system\n- `Badge` → Achievements\n- Leaderboards\n\n**5. Custom App (fg_companion):**\n- `FG Event` → Calendar events\n- `FG Event Attendee` → RSVP tracking\n- `FG Mentor Match` → Mentorship system\n- `FG AI Settings` → AI moderation\n- `FG User Settings` → User preferences\n- `FG SSO Provider` → Social login\n\n## Data Flow:\n\n**1. User signs in** → Frappe `User` table\n**2. User browses `/spaces/:spaceId`** → Frappe `GP Project` GET\n**3. User creates post** → `GP Discussion` INSERT + background sentiment job\n**4. System moderates** → `FG Moderation Queue` + Helpdesk ticket\n**5. Post appears** → Frappe `GP Discussion` list with EPS points awarded\n**6. User earns badge** → `FG Badge Award` INSERT\n\n## Key Features:\n\n- **One auth model** → All surfaces use same User table\n- **Real-time updates** → WebSockets, push notifications\n- **Background jobs** → Sentiment analysis, vector search, digests\n- **Content moderation** → AI sentiment + Helpdesk integration\n- **Gamification** → EPS points, badges, leaderboards\n- **Payments** → Stripe integration for courses/events\n- **Mobile** → PWA + Raven mobile app\n\nThe **prototype** (`community-launchpad-proto`) is just the frontend with mock data. The **production system** will swap in the real Frappe backend while keeping the same TypeScript types.\n\nWould you like me to explain any specific component in detail?",
