      "type": "answer",
      "text": "The bench was initialized but the `fg_companion` app doesn't exist yet. Here's how to set it up:\n\n## Current Structure:\n\n```\n~/my-bench/\n├── apps/\n│   ├── frappe/\n│   ├── gameplan/     # Frappe ecosystem apps\n│   ├── lms/\n│   ├── raven/\n│   └── ... (Frappe apps)\n├── sites/\n└── ...\n```\n\n## Create the fg_companion App:\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to bench root\ncd ~/my-bench\n\n# Create the fg_companion app structure\nmkdir -p apps/fg_companion/fg_companion\n\n# Initialize a standard Python package\ncd apps/fg_companion\npip install frappe\npip install frappe-gameplan\npip install frappe-lms\npip install frappe-raven\n\n# Create setup.py\ncat > setup.py << 'EOF'\nfrom setuptools import setup, find_packages\n\nsetup(\n    name=\"fg_companion\",\n    version=\"1.0.0\",\n    packages=find_packages(),\n    include_package_data=True,\n    install_requires=[\n        \"frappe>=16.0.0\",\n        \"frappe-gameplan>=16.0.0\",\n        \"frappe-lms>=16.0.0\",\n        \"frappe-raven>=16.0.0\"\n    ],\n    entry_points={\n        \"console_scripts\": [\n            \"fg_companion = fg_companion.__main__:main\"\n        ]\n    }\n)\nEOF\n\n# Create __init__.py\ntouch fg_companion/__init__.py\n\n# Initialize as a Frappe app\ntouch fg_companion/__init__.py\n```\n\n## Create the Frontend Structure:\n\n```bash\n# Create the frontend directory\nmkdir -p fg_companion/frontend\n\n# Copy your Vue.js prototype\ncd fg_companion\ncp -r ~/community-launchpad-proto/* frontend/\n```\n\n## Install Node Dependencies:\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to frontend\ncd frontend\n\n# Initialize package.json with all your Vue.js dependencies\ncat > package.json << 'EOF'\n{\n  \"name\": \"fg_companion\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"vite dev\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\n    \"preview\": \"vite preview\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"vue\": \"^3.4.21\",\n    \"@vueuse/core\": \"^10.9.0\",\n    \"frappe-ui\": \"latest\",\n    \"class-variance-authority\": \"^0.7.1\",\n    \"clsx\": \"^2.1.1\",\n    \"date-fns\": \"^4.1.0\",\n    \"tailwind-merge\": \"^3.5.0\",\n    \"tailwindcss\": \"^4.2.1\",\n    \"tw-animate-css\": \"^1.3.4\",\n    \"vue-router\": \"^4.3.0\",\n    \"zod\": \"^3.24.2\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-vue\": \"^5.0.4\",\n    \"@vue/compiler-sfc\": \"^3.4.21\",\n    \"@eslint/js\": \"^9.32.0\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.16.5\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^8.61.1\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^8.61.1\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^9.32.0\",\n    \"eslint-config-prettier\": \"^10.1.1\",\n    \"eslint-plugin-prettier\": \"^5.2.6\",\n    \"eslint-plugin-vue\": \"^10.9.2\",\n    \"globals\": \"^15.15.0\",\n    \"prettier\": \"^3.7.3\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^6.0.3\",\n    \"vite\": \"^8.0.16\",\n    \"vue-eslint-parser\": \"^10.4.1\"\n  }\n}\nEOF\n\n# Install dependencies\nyarn install\n```\n\n## Configure vite.config.ts:\n\n```bash\n# Create vite.config.ts in frontend\ncat > frontend/vite.config.ts << 'EOF'\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vite';\nimport vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue';\nimport path from 'path';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [vue()],\n  resolve: {\n    alias: {\n      '@': path.resolve(__dirname, './src'),\n    },\n  },\n  build: {\n    // Output to Frappe's public assets\n    outDir: '../fg_companion/public/frontend',\n    emptyOutDir: true,\n  },\n});\nEOF\n```\n\n## Test:\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to bench root\ncd ~/my-bench\n\n# Install the fg_companion app\nbench get-app fg_companion\n\n# Build everything\nbench build\n\n# Start the bench\nbench start\n```\n\nNow you'll have the complete Frappe ecosystem with your Vue.js prototype integrated!",
      "timestamp": 1781971422490
    },
