      "text": "The PowerShell commands are not working properly. Let me try a different approach. It seems like there might be an issue with the PowerShell environment. Let me try to work around this by trying to understand the structure from what we already know.\n\nFrom the previous output, we saw that the bench was initialized successfully and various apps were mentioned in the README. However, the actual apps directory might not be set up yet. Let me try to understand the structure and provide guidance.\n\nThe user is asking where they are at and where they should be working. Given that the bench was initialized with `bench init my-bench`, the typical structure would be:\n\n```\n~/my-bench/\n├── apps/\n│   ├── frappe/\n│   ├── frappe/\n│   ├── gameplan/\n│   └── ...\n└── sites/\n└── ...\n```\n\nThe fg_companion app doesn't exist yet, so I should explain how to create it and what the expected structure is.",
