      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "does my app have the pythoon code?\n\nYou are right to be cautious—we need to be clear about the distinction between\nwhat we installed and what your app actually is.\n\nWhat we did (The Backend Infrastructure)\n\nWe just successfully built a Frappe \"Bench\" (the engine).\n\n  - We installed the Frappe Framework (the foundation).\n  - We installed Gameplan, LMS, and Raven as independent apps (the community,\n    learning, and messaging modules).\n  - We created your fg_companion app (the custom \"glue\" app you started).\n\nHow your fg_companion app integrates everything\n\nAt the moment, fg_companion is an empty shell generated by bench new-app. It is\ncurrently a container waiting for your code.\n\nIt does not \"know\" about Gameplan or LMS yet. You have to bridge them. Here is\nhow your app fg_companion will actually integrate the rest:\n\n1. Dependencies (The \"Mix\")\n\nIn your fg_companion app, you need to tell Frappe that your app depends on the\nothers. This allows your app to \"see\" and extend the features of Gameplan, LMS,\netc.\n\n  - Open the file: ~/my-bench/apps/fg_companion/fg_companion/hooks.py\n  - Look for the required_apps section and make sure it looks like this:\n\nrequired_apps = [\"frappe\", \"gameplan\", \"lms\", \"raven\"]\n\n2. The Integration (The \"Hub\")\n\nBecause you are using the Frappe Framework, you don't need to manually code the\nconnections. Frappe's DocType system handles the \"convergence\" for you\nautomatically:\n\n  - If you want to add Mentorship to an LMS Course: You create an FG Mentor\n    Match DocType in your fg_companion app and add a Link field to the LMS\n    Course DocType. Frappe automatically creates the relationship in the\n    database for you.\n  - If you want to track Points (EPS) for a Discussion post: You write a simple\n    Python function in your fg_companion app that listens for the on_submit\n    event of GP Discussion (from the Gameplan app) and awards EPS Energy Point\n    (from the EPS app).\n\nIs your code in the fg_companion folder?\n\nRight now, you copied your frontend prototype into\n~/my-bench/apps/fg_companion/frontend.\n\nDoes your fg_companion app also have the Python backend code (the API endpoints,\nthe custom DocType logic, etc.)?\n\n  - If yes: You need to copy that code into the\n    ~/my-bench/apps/fg_companion/fg_companion/ folder.\n  - If no: We need to help you move that backend logic from your Windows\n    repository into the correct folders inside the Linux fg_companion app\n    directory so the backend knows how to handle the data for Gameplan, LMS, and\n    Raven.\n\nWhich part are you most concerned about right now—the frontend \"hub\" layout or\nthe backend logic that connects the LMS/Gameplan apps?\n",
